Class GitCheckout

java.lang.Object
  edu.nyu.cs.javagit.api.commands.GitCheckout

public final class GitCheckout
extends java.lang.Object

GitCheckout provides an interface for checking out files from a particular branch in the repository or creating a new branch and switching to it.

checkout

public GitCheckoutResponse checkout(java.io.File repositoryPath,
                                    GitCheckoutOptions options,
                                    Ref branch)
                             throws java.io.IOException,
                                    JavaGitException
For checking out a branch or creating a new branch. The is the value of the option '-b' passed in GitCheckoutOptions starting at provided as the last argument to the checkout method.

Parameters:
repositoryPath - Path to the Git repository.
options - GitCheckoutOptions passed.
branch - name of the branch that will be checked out OR if creating a new branch then the starting for the new branch will be this branch.
Returns:
GitCheckoutResponse object
Throws:
JavaGitException - thrown if -
  • if the output for <git-checkout> command generated an error.
  • if options provided are incorrect.
  • if processBuilder not able to run the command.
    • java.io.IOException - thrown if -
    • paths given do not have proper permissions.
    • paths given do not exist at all.
